name: Rackspace Email Hosting Customer Segment
description: Aggregate customer segment representing tens of thousands of business domains using Rackspace Email hosted email service. Identified via OSINT through reverse MX record analysis showing domains resolving to mx1.emailsrvr.com and mx2.emailsrvr.com. Primarily SMB and mid-market organizations. Served from Rackspace-owned data centers on AS33070 (DFW) and AS27357 (IAD) infrastructure. com MX record analysis, ipinfo.io ASN domain enumeration, Rackspace Email product page.

name: Rackspace Cloud Hosting Customer Segment (DFW)
description: Aggregate customer segment representing approximately 381,358 hosted domains across 16,257 IP addresses on AS33070 (RACKSPACE-DFW, Dallas/Fort Worth). Infrastructure includes 799,685 IPv4 addresses across 96 prefixes and 7,128 nameservers. Domains identified via stabletransit.com and rackspace.com nameserver delegation. Customers span IaaS, PaaS and legacy cloud hosting. com AS33070 analysis, ipinfo.io domain enumeration, BigDataCloud IPv4 allocation data.

name: Rackspace Cloud Hosting Customer Segment (IAD)
description: Aggregate customer segment representing approximately 84,162 hosted domains across 6,014 IP addresses on AS27357 (RACKSPACE-IAD, Ashburn/Northern Virginia). Customers span IaaS, PaaS and legacy cloud hosting workloads served from the Northern Virginia data center cluster. io AS27357 domain enumeration, dnslytics.com ASN analysis.

name: FedRAMP Government Customer Segment
description: Aggregate customer segment representing 40+ federal, state and local government organizations using Rackspace Government Cloud (RGC) on VMware. FedRAMP Joint Authorization Board authorized since 2015. Supports DoD Impact Level 4, DFARS, and CMMC compliance requirements. Customer identities anonymized per government compliance convention. com/cloud/rackspace-government-cloud, FedRAMP Marketplace listing.

name: Fortune 100 Customer Segment
description: Aggregate customer segment representing more than half of the Fortune 100 companies as disclosed in SEC filings and corporate communications. Individual customer identities not publicly disclosed due to no single customer exceeding 2% of net revenue. Revenue generated across 120+ countries with majority from US and UK operations. com/about/why-rackspace-technology.

provenance.primary_data_source: Rackspace 10-K FY2024, S-1 2020 registration statement, rackspace

name: Rackspace Cloud DNS Customer Segment
